cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with scene text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves sequential modeling and memory accessing mechanisms, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new architecture to improve OCR, which is a classic problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses neural networks to solve the OCR problem, which falls under the subfield of deep learning (cs.NE).
